Long ago, the radiant Auroras—a dazzling tapestry woven from Elara’s luminous spirit and the Great Cosmic Raven’s silver feathers—stood as an impenetrable shield across the heavens. Banished from the skies, the vengeful Frost Serpents slithered deep into the earth’s abyssal caverns. There, they waited for the auroral lights to wane with the turning of the year, exhaling a bitter, icy venom upward through the dense bedrock.

This creeping frost choked ancient roots and muted rushing rivers, plunging the mortal realm into a biting, relentless winter. Refusing to let her beloved world succumb to an eternal freeze, Elara summoned her trusted ally, the Cosmic Raven. She blessed its vast wings with concentrated, golden solar warmth. As the massive bird soared above the shivering lands, it cast down a brilliant shower of glowing embers.

Wherever these radiant feathers touched the frost, the treacherous ice melted, allowing vibrant green shoots to burst forth and herald the return of Spring. Sinking deep into the subterranean darkness, the warm embers struck the Serpents’ icy scales. Instantly, they crystallized into brilliant veins of Sun-stone and shimmering quartz, forging a luminous underground prison. Today, mortals mine these stones to survive winter chills, trusting Elara’s light.

